109796.name: Death rate – Outdoor air pollution (age-standardized) (IHME)
109796.description: Age-standardized death rates from outdoor air pollution, measured as the number of deaths per 100,000.

source.name: Outdoor air pollution deaths (IHME, 2019)
source.dataPublishedBy: Global Burden of Disease Collaborative Network. Global Burden of Disease Study 2017 (GBD 2017) Results. Seattle, United States: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation (IHME), 2018.
source.additionalInfo:
Data on total outdoor (ambient) air pollution deaths and death rates were calculated by Our World in Data based on two metrics published by the IHME, Global Burden of Disease study.

Total outdoor air pollution deaths are given as the sum of 'Ambient ozone pollution deaths' and 'Ambient particulate matter pollution deaths'. The same applies to the calculate of total outdoor pollution rates.
